<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36203g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36203g">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36203g"> 203(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cocks turned into hens / ran cackling in street</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The streets of New Amsterdam now presented a scene of wild dismay and consternation. In vain did Peter Stuyvesant order the citizens to arm and assemble on the Battery. Blank terror reigned over the community. The whole party of Short Pipes in the course of a single night had changed into arrant old women&mdash;a metamorphosis only to be paralleled by the prodigies recorded by Livy as having happened at Rome at the approach of Hannibal, when statues sweated in pure affright, goats were converted into sheep, and <mark>cocks, turning into hens, ran cackling about the street</mark>. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 409</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09113b" href="c09all.htm#c09113b">VI.C.09:113(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
